==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: kweek
<hw>kweek</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A trailing grass (<spn>Cynodon
dactylon</spn>) native to Europe, now cosmopolitan in warm regions; used
for lawns and pastures especially in the Southern U. S. and India.
Called also <altname>Bahama grass</altname> and <altname>Bermuda
grass</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Bermuda grass, devil grass, Bahama grass, doob,
scutch grass, star grass, <spn>Cynodon dactylon</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>kwela</ent>⟦br⟧
